Class FarkleDiceLogic

  • java.lang.Object
    • farklegame.FarkleDiceLogic

  • public class FarkleDiceLogic
extends java.lang.Object
    The FarkleDiceLogic class performs our actual game logic on Dice class objects. The requirements for this was obtained from an external source on Farkle game rules.

      • isFarkle

        public boolean isFarkle​(java.util.ArrayList<Dice> hand)
        isFarkle is called in order to detect if a Farkle has been rolled. It will call upon scoreHandAll, and compare it to roundPoints, if they're equal that means that zero points have been scored this turn, and that it is a Farkle. If it is a Farkle, you add 1 to the Farkle counters, at 3 Farkles you remove 1000 points from bankedPoints and reset the counter. After a Farkle has been detected, it resets the round, and returns true. If there was no Farkle, it just returns false.
        Parameters:
        hand - is the arraylist of dice being passed to isFarkle
        Returns:
        Returns whether or not there has been a farkle.

      • scoreHand

        public int scoreHand​(java.util.ArrayList<Dice> hand)
        ScoreHand determines points based off of which dice are held. hande is first sent through an forloop, creating an array that has the non-held number of each dice. dice[0] = 4 would mean there are 4 "1" dice. "1" dice and "5" dice are sent through their own switch-case, because they are graded differently. While in the switch case they are counted for pairs and straights. For details on specific score values read the official Farkle rules. After going through the forloop they are compared for which value is greater (but only for dice that can count for multiple values), and the greater value is scored
        Parameters:
        hand - is the hand of dice passed to it.
        Returns:
        Returns the score integer.

      • bankPoints

        public void bankPoints​()
        bankPoints is used to take the current round points and point them into the total bankpoints. It will also reset your round points and check to see if points are over 10,000 which would be a victory
